1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:01,440
Looks like the neighbors

2
00:00:01,720 --> 00:00:04,400
have a kid your age.

3
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:06,160
Someone like Ko doesn’t

4
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:07,320
just become friends with anyone.

5
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:10,520
Oops.

6
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:12,440
What are you doing?

7
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,800
I’m just walking home.

8
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:16,600
Are we close? Why talk to me so casually?

9
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:19,560
Everyone’s beloved Ko here,

10
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:21,400
what’s he like at home?

11
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:25,200
Ever since I moved here,

12
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:27,720
I’ve seen him stay up late every night.

13
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:35,840
His light’s always on. I think he’s studying.

14
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:38,120
Thanks for what you told the teacher.

15
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,040
Are you new?

16
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:44,880
I don’t think I’ve seen you before.

17
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,720
I’ve been going to
the same school as you, Augar.

18
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:47,640
You know my name?

19
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:48,920
Achi.

20
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,600
I promise I’ll recognize you next time.

21
00:00:51,160 --> 00:00:51,960
Come say hi to me anytime.

22
00:00:58,040 --> 00:00:58,920
I’m not stealing it.

23
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:01,400
Let’s just call it payment for washing that dude’s face.

24
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:01,800
Stop it.

25
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:02,440
Just a little more.

26
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,800
But one orange isn’t gonna cut it.

27
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,200
(My dad always reads in the morning
whenever he’s back from the sea.)

28
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:38,080
(He once told me people have a 26% chance
of waking up early on summer mornings.)

29
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:41,280
(That’s not enough for someone like me.)

30
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:56,160
(There’s also an 18% chance
people get cranky during summer.)

31
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:59,400
(That number’s way too low for my mom.)

32
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:03,320
Honey, Ko, come eat
before the food gets cold.

33
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,200
Yes, Mom.

34
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:10,120
(But the chance of someone staying calm
during this season is only 3%.)

35
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,080
Mom, I’m heading to school. It’s the first day.

36
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:13,160
Aren’t you gonna sit down and eat first?

37
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,000
No, it’s okay.

38
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:24,440
I’m off, Dad.

39
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:25,560
Bye-bye.

40
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:26,280
Mm-hmm.

41
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,240
Hey, Ko.

42
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,880
You almost ran over my foot.

43
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:32,800
This kid.

44
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,600
He’s just like his dad.

45
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:36,840
And what’s wrong with that, honey?

46
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:41,040
Come on, let him be.

47
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:42,640
He probably misses his friends.

48
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:46,880
Just like his dad always misses his friends.

49
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,560
Mm, let’s eat breakfast.

50
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,200
Come on.

51
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,400
(I don’t know where Dad got all that from,)

52
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:56,320
(or if he just made it up when I was little,
but I’ve always believed him.)

53
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:04,640
(And the chance of me looking
handsome on the first day of school…)

54
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:10,960
(is definitely 100%.)

55
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:13,000
You two, wait your turn.

56
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:19,320
[BARBERSHOP]

57
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:29,040
You two, make way.

58
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:29,760
Yeah, move.

59
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:44,240
Four-eyes, outta my way.

60
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,640
This is the life!

61
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,160
Come on, sir.

62
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:56,080
Why not use scissors?

63
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:59,120
Already causing trouble on day one?

64
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:01,000
Your friend was talking you up the other day.

65
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:02,560
Come on.

66
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,000
He’s not my friend.

67
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,160
You’ll be friends eventually.

68
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:06,440
Here.

69
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,320
Mr. Kong, please.

70
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,520
I’ll fix it in the evening. Please.

71
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,760
I promise. I promise.

72
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,680
I’ll be back.

73
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,280
Don’t forget to come back.

74
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:26,600
This desk is mine.

75
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:30,360
Like anyone would dare steal from Boss Ko.

76
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:31,800
Suit yourself.

77
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:35,160
Augar, why aren’t you sitting with me?

78
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,240
I’m gonna sleep.

79
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:41,560
August!

80
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,800
Get over here.

81
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:48,120
Empty brains shouldn’t stick together.
We’ll get even dumber.

82
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,400
This dude.

83
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,120
Fine, whatever.

84
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,720
Who do you think
our homeroom teacher’s gonna be?

85
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:57,000
Anyone but Mr. Prateep. He scares me.

86
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,600
You know Majin Buu?

87
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,760
Who do you think our homeroom teacher is?

88
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,000
Mr. Prateep?

89
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:12,360
Or Mr. Kong?

90
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,920
I hope it’s Mr. Kong.

91
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:15,960
You think so? Yeah?

92
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,360
What are you reading?

93
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:27,240
Anatomy, about scientists dissecting
students who don’t pay attention in class.

94
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:30,400
They found that serotonin levels
in their prefrontal cortex are low...

95
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:32,960
Okay, then. Keep reading.

96
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:34,400
I won’t bother you anymore.

97
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:40,880
Augar.

98
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:43,160
Wanna switch seats?

99
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:46,240
What are you talking about? No way.

100
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:47,160
Asshole.

101
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:51,600
Ahem.

102
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:58,880
Mr. Kong, are you our homeroom teacher?

103
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:00,520
[MONDAY, MAY 15, 2000]

104
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:01,160
That’s right.

105
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,200
All right.

106
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:09,160
Before we begin,
let’s choose the class president.

107
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:11,960
I nominate myself.

108
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:15,920
I’ll take care of everyone in this class.

109
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:17,200
Come on.

110
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:20,040
I’d like to nominate too.

111
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:28,520
I mean... I nominate Tle for class president.

112
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:29,800
I agree, sir.

113
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:30,920
Me too.

114
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,640
Same here.

115
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:33,960
Okay then.

116
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,080
Tle, you’re the class president.

117
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:39,640
August, August.

118
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:40,360
Listen, everyone.

119
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:41,200
(Bastard.)

120
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:44,680
I forgot to mention, we have
a new transfer student joining the class.

121
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,480
Come introduce yourself.

122
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:52,800
Good morning.

123
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:55,040
My name is Kanin Siritara.

124
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:55,880
And your nickname?

125
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:57,960
It’s Ko.

126
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,200
(You again?)

127
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,760
Well, well.

128
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:10,680
Looks like you’re not the only Ko
at this school anymore.

129
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,800
He’s clenching his fist.

130
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,600
There’s an empty seat over there.

131
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,200
You can sit there for now.

132
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:23,240
We’ll rearrange seats later since
three students still haven’t shown up yet.

133
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:24,480
Yes, sir.

134
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:40,560
Jeez.

135
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,400
You followed me here too?

136
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:57,400
I moved here, and this is the nearest school.

137
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:02,200
But that seat’s taken.

138
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,960
Mr. Kong said more people are coming.

139
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,040
I’ll move later.

140
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:09,440
Good.

141
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:13,600
The paper I just handed out
is your timetable for this semester.

142
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:14,880
Pass it to your classmates.

143
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,960
Come on, Mr. Kong.

144
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,280
Who made this schedule?

145
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:21,160
Math after PE? We can’t do that.

146
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,160
It’s good.

147
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:24,600
Train your body first, then train your brain.

148
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:27,000
Good point, sir.

149
00:09:27,160 --> 00:09:28,880
Get ready for first period.

150
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:30,760
Try acting like 10th graders.

151
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:33,200
Okay, that’s it for now.

152
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,920
Class.

153
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:37,520
- Thank you, sir.
- Thank you, sir.

154
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:51,560
Pair up with the person next to you.

155
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,360
Hey, Augar.

156
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:03,960
Ma’am, can’t we pick our own partners?

157
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:08,240
Pair up with whoever you want.

158
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:10,200
Once you’ve got a partner, sit down.

159
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:14,640
Excuse me.

160
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:15,240
Hey.

161
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:16,680
Dammit.

162
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,000
Hey!

163
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:22,080
You two, why don’t you sit down?

164
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,240
What are you waiting for?

165
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:27,160
Ma’am, can’t we just pair up randomly?

166
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:29,040
Randomly?

167
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:30,520
Yes, ma’am.

168
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:34,000
I’ll pair you up
according to your class numbers.

169
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:37,760
First, number 9.

170
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:38,440
That’s me, sir.

171
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:38,960
Ah!

172
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:41,880
Number 32.

173
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,440
Who’s 32?

174
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:47,160
Alright, you two do this assignment together.

175
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,440
Next.

176
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,200
Holy crap.

177
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:53,200
I got paired with him
in three subjects already.

178
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:56,080
But he seems smart.

179
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:57,320
That could actually be a good thing.

180
00:10:57,560 --> 00:11:01,520
Boss Ko, do you believe everything
is planned by the universe like I do?

181
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:05,680
Maybe this is destiny.

182
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:06,920
More like “messtiny.”

183
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,120
Don’t piss me off.

184
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:11,240
There’s no way
someone like me would like him.

185
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,560
Classic.

186
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:17,160
Dammit. And it’s hot out here.

187
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:20,880
Before you head home, come to
the library with me and borrow a book.

188
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:21,920
We need it for the assignment.

189
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:24,760
No.

190
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:27,120
Why can’t you go by yourself?

191
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,160
It’s a pair assignment.

192
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:32,800
But it’s the first day of school.
Why are you in such a hurry?

193
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,400
What?

194
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:38,760
I’m only letting this slide once.

195
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:41,080
You two stick together like fried dough sticks.

196
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:42,840
You’re paired up in every subject.

197
00:11:44,960 --> 00:11:46,000
(Screw you.)

198
00:11:57,960 --> 00:11:58,920
[LIBRARY]

199
00:11:58,920 --> 00:11:59,600
Is it closed?

200
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:04,240
It’s your fault we’re late.

201
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,440
What? How is this my fault?

202
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,680
You weren’t in the classroom.

203
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:09,200
You were hanging around out here.

204
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:12,520
You can come back tomorrow.
Why are you taking this so seriously?

205
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,200
Besides, we’ve got

206
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:16,600
plenty of time to work on it.

207
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,040
We should get started
right away when we have time.

208
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:20,240
Don’t wait until the last minute

209
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,080
That’s a bad habit.

210
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:24,480
Are you freaking lecturing me right now?

211
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,680
I told you to watch your language.

212
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,400
We’re not that close.

213
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:30,800
Wait.

214
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,720
You need the book?

215
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,680
Fine. I’ll get it for you.

216
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:51,480
Hold my bag.

217
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,280
Do you play volleyball?

218
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:55,960
What?

219
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:58,120
Do you?

220
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:00,560
I’ve played before.

221
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:02,680
Make a platform.

222
00:13:05,560 --> 00:13:06,200
Like this?

223
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:09,640
No, like this.

224
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,320
Perfect.

225
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:13,960
Hey.

226
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:15,720
Keep your grip strong

227
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:23,840
Just give me a second.

228
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,360
I forgot which book it was.

229
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:27,040
This is literally stealing.

230
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,000
Come out.

231
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:31,520
Stealing, my ass. It’s called borrowing.

232
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:34,680
This?

233
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:35,520
My right.

234
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:38,040
Then you should’ve said my left.

235
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,800
Get out already.

236
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,080
All done.

237
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:52,400
Come on, let’s go.

238
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:54,680
What if we got caught?

239
00:13:56,080 --> 00:14:00,280
Hey, someone like Ko
knows every corner of this school.

240
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:03,880
Don’t you worry, sidekick.

241
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:04,360
What?

242
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:10,160
I’m not using any rude words.

243
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:15,440
You handle this partner assignment.

244
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:17,240
Consider it payback for wasting my time.

245
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:19,240
Boss Ko’s got other stuff to do.

246
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:33,560
[BARBERSHOP]

247
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,440
Uncle, is there a queue?

248
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:38,280
Go sit down.

249
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:46,600
What style do you want, Ko?

250
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,120
The usual.

251
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,200
The usual?

252
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:51,480
All done then. Get up.

253
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:55,200
Come on, uncle. That joke’s ancient.

254
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,560
All right, all right.

255
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:58,200
Let’s do it.

256
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:14,000
I’m here for a haircut, please.

257
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,440
I thought you came to do laundry.

258
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:17,640
No, sir. I’m here for a haircut.

259
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:20,400
You again?

260
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,800
Go somewhere else.
The queue’s too long here.

261
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:25,800
-Ko, you little rascal.
-Ow!

262
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,880
Come on. Sit right here, boy.

263
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:35,720
Noodles!

264
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,800
Perfect timing. Give me a sec.

265
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,680
Hang on, kid. I’m starving.

266
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,760
Come on, uncle. I’m in a rush.

267
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,640
What’s with those two?

268
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,360
Hey, what’re you staring at?

269
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:53,200
Not you.

270
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,360
What about our homework? You done yet?

271
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:57,080
No.

272
00:15:57,760 --> 00:15:59,040
My mom made me get a haircut first.

273
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:03,240
You’re cold.

274
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,120
I haven’t even gotten a thank-you.

275
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:06,560
For what?

276
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:07,520
For the book.

277
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,200
I broke into the library for you.

278
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,280
I never asked you to do it like that.

279
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:14,440
You’re smart, but your focus is totally off.

280
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:15,960
Focus on the result.

281
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:22,600
You’re stubborn.

282
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:24,840
Talk nicely to me.

283
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:28,760
Actually, I’ve helped you twice already.

284
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:30,960
Hm?

285
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,040
Come on.

286
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:40,800
Hurry it up.

287
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:45,080
I’m only paying half if you’re this slow.

288
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:47,760
Fine. I’ll cut your hair for free.

289
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:48,200
Really?

290
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,320
I’ll just charge your dad instead.

291
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:40,360
I’ll call this your thank-you.

292
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:57,480
Where’s your dear friend, Boss Ko?

293
00:17:58,120 --> 00:17:59,240
Dear friend, my ass.

294
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:03,320
You done with the homework? Can I copy it?

295
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:06,600
No idea. I told the new guy to do it.

296
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,400
Abusing your power already.

297
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:13,040
Hey, hey!

298
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,600
The new kid’s getting jumped
by some 11th graders.

299
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:15,520
- What?
- What?

300
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,280
Yeah, the new guy Ko.

301
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:20,960
Damn it.

302
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:23,920
Why the f*ck are you trying to play hero?

303
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:26,160
Then why were you messing with him?

304
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:27,720
I didn’t do anything.

305
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:28,560
Right?

306
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:31,680
I was just borrowing a little money from him.

307
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:33,560
This kid’s loaded.

308
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,600
But he wouldn’t hand it over.

309
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:38,600
Then he suddenly walked straight into my fist.

310
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:43,640
Just like you who walked right into my friend’s fist.

311
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:44,560
Right, Achi?

312
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,120
Right?

313
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:50,240
What a loser.

314
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:54,280
What the f*ck are you guys doing?

315
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:15,560
Ganging up on them, you assholes?

316
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,400
A whole pack against two? Very classy.

317
00:19:17,640 --> 00:19:19,640
Right. Don’t come any closer.

318
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:25,160
Pathetic losers.

319
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,520
You came looking for trouble.

320
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:28,000
Wanna play heroes, huh?

321
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:29,000
Bring it on.

322
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:30,040
Come on.

323
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:43,320
Stop it! What are you guys doing?

324
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:46,600
Knock it off! Break it up!

325
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:47,560
Back off!

326
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:48,640
Back off!

327
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:53,160
You 11th graders again?

328
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:54,480
Want to get suspended again?

329
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:58,280
All of you, come with me to my office.

330
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:05,040
I’m not gonna hit you like
when you were little kids anymore.

331
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:12,680
I trust you’re old enough to know right from wrong.

332
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:16,440
This is your first warning.

333
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:24,880
11th graders,
write your names down for the record.

334
00:20:26,520 --> 00:20:29,640
10th graders, head to the infirmary,
then go back to classes.

335
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:31,480
Thank you, sir.

336
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:32,920
Goodbye.

337
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:42,160
Ow, that hurts.

338
00:20:42,360 --> 00:20:42,960
Sorry.

339
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:47,400
Jeez, Achi.

340
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:48,840
Why didn’t you fight back?

341
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,280
You remembered my name?

342
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:57,400
I told you I’d recognize you
when we met again.

343
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:00,320
Mm.

344
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:06,960
Someone like you
gets fired up enough to fight, huh?

345
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:09,720
They harassed Achi first.

346
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:15,240
Do you even know him?
Why’d you stick your nose in and help him?

347
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:17,760
No.

348
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:21,560
But if I hadn’t stepped in,
Achi would’ve gotten beat up even worse.

349
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:24,400
Right, big hero.

350
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:31,000
You barely react.
Don’t you feel anything at all?

351
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:34,240
A little.

352
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:40,680
What am I supposed to do here?

353
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:44,360
Miss, someone just lost his leg!

354
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:48,960
Even that wouldn’t wake her up.

355
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:55,920
That new guy’s pretty awesome.

356
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:57,200
He even protected Achi.

357
00:21:57,840 --> 00:21:58,200
Yeah.

358
00:21:58,640 --> 00:22:01,560
By the way, Boss Ko,
you were seriously cool back there.

359
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,360
That was nothing.

360
00:22:04,080 --> 00:22:07,080
I could’ve taken all of them on at once.

361
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:09,560
- Aw!
- Aw!

362
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:11,960
My boss is such a gangster.

363
00:22:16,720 --> 00:22:18,080
Why aren’t you guys back in class?

364
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:22,360
Hey, if we’re getting punished,
we might as well make the most of it.

365
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:26,160
Then... these are all on me.

366
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:26,840
Hey.

367
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:30,760
See? Now that’s someone who adapts fast.

368
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:33,600
Really? Thanks.

369
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:34,920
Sit down.

370
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:47,440
Hey, after all that,
why don’t you two join my gang?

371
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:52,120
Don’t get the wrong idea.

372
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:55,040
I didn’t help you
because I wanted you in my gang.

373
00:22:58,640 --> 00:23:01,640
I was just worried no one
would do my homework for me.

374
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:08,600
Hey, come on. Sit down.

375
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:15,600
Honestly, Ko’s not even that tough.

376
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:16,880
He just acts like it.

377
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:19,320
Hey, I heard that, August.

378
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:21,960
Who said anything?

379
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:36,440
What’s up with you?

380
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:38,280
I’m going home.

381
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:40,000
Mm.

382
00:23:44,680 --> 00:23:45,320
What now?

383
00:23:46,760 --> 00:23:48,040
I’m going home with you.

384
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:53,960
What about your bike?

385
00:23:57,560 --> 00:23:58,400
I’ll leave it here.

386
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:02,240
Today, I wanna go home with
the newest member of my group.

387
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:06,240
Aren’t you scared it’ll get stolen?

388
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:08,640
Who’d dare steal from Boss Ko?

389
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:17,880
If you ever have any problems,
just tell me. Got it?

390
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:20,800
Mm.

391
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:30,000
We’re shaking on it.

392
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:33,600
From now on, I’ll take care of you.

393
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:37,120
Mm.

394
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:41,160
Come on, let’s head home.

395
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,160
Hey, give me your bag. I’ll carry it for you.

396
00:24:52,520 --> 00:24:54,000
Make it fast, boy.

397
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:02,200
Are you down about
getting a warning today?

398
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:06,600
No. Mr. Prateep was pretty fair.

399
00:25:06,760 --> 00:25:07,640
He called out what was wrong.

400
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:21,440
What about the homework? Need any help?

401
00:25:21,880 --> 00:25:24,000
No. I finished it last night.

402
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:25,400
But I haven’t done the other subjects yet.

403
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:27,720
Good job, Ko Song.

404
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:29,280
What’s with you?

405
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,880
One minute you call me a sidekick,
the next you call me Ko Song.

406
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:34,120
Forget the rest.

407
00:25:34,560 --> 00:25:36,440
From now on, you’re Ko Song.

408
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,120
Why “Song”?

409
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:40,280
Because I’m “Neung.”

410
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,200
But I was born first.

411
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:44,320
Yeah, but I lived here first,
so I’m number one.

412
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,680
Fine. Call me whatever you want.

413
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:47,440
Suit yourself.

414
00:25:58,520 --> 00:26:02,440
Then tomorrow, come pick up Ko Neung.
Got it, Ko Song?

415
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:05,040
Fine. I will.

416
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:08,840
That’s more like it, Ko Song.

417
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:18,360
Here.

418
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:22,880
Thanks for the ride.

419
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:26,280
See you tomorrow, Ko Song.

420
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:28,440
Bye-bye.

421
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:46,640
So, how was school, Boss Ko?

422
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:48,280
Is 10th grade too hard for you?

423
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:51,160
Is there anything Ko can’t handle?

424
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:55,680
Come out to sea and fish with me.

425
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:59,840
No way. It takes forever,
and there are mosquitoes everywhere.

426
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,520
I’m a hot-blooded teenager.

427
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:02,960
I’m not calm like you, Dad.

428
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,960
Ko, why don’t you at least try it first?

429
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:08,600
Honey, stop bothering him.

430
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:10,680
He’s a teenager.
He wants to hang out with his friends.

431
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:11,520
You get him, huh?

432
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:12,520
Yeah.

433
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:13,720
Why don’t you
head out to sea with me instead?

434
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:14,440
Ko!

435
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:17,640
Ko!

436
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:19,800
Dad, Mom, I’m heading out.

437
00:27:20,120 --> 00:27:20,400
Bye-bye.

438
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:20,720
What?

439
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:21,800
Finished already?

440
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:22,440
Mm.

441
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:30,720
Hop on.

442
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:33,760
- Honey.
- Hm?

443
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:37,880
When did our Ko
become friends with the boy next door?

444
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:42,840
If you don’t know,
how am I supposed to know?

445
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:55,760
Guys!

446
00:27:56,880 --> 00:28:00,080
Listen up and rejoice.

447
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:04,800
From now on, I’m Ko Neung,

448
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:09,440
and this guy’s Ko Song.

449
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:11,880
Jeez.

450
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:17,480
That’s awesome, boss.

451
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:18,600
Haha!

452
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:26,200
You’re old news now, Augar.

453
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:30,280
Yeah. Guess I’m a stray dog now. Damn!

454
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:37,320
Achi, what are you doing in this class?

455
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:43,920
I asked my mom to talk to the principal
so I could transfer here

456
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:45,720
and be with you guys.

457
00:28:49,080 --> 00:28:50,360
Hey, move over there.

458
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:02,000
I’m the real stray dog now.

459
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:04,960
Nice one, Achi.

460
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:08,040
You’re a valuable member of the gang.

461
00:29:08,400 --> 00:29:11,520
Our gang’s about to double in size.

462
00:29:11,920 --> 00:29:14,320
Soon, nobody’ll dare mess with us.

463
00:29:15,160 --> 00:29:16,520
I’ll look after you all.

464
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:19,840
All right, be quiet.

465
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:23,120
Take out your books and get ready for class.

466
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:28,080
Don’t forget, we still have
partner assignments for two more subjects.

467
00:29:29,760 --> 00:29:31,840
All right, I won’t forget.

468
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:37,200
Everyone, turn to page 13.

469
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:46,640
Are you taking your bike home?

470
00:29:51,120 --> 00:29:51,520
Yeah.

471
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:52,960
It’s not that I’m scared it’ll get stolen.

472
00:29:54,040 --> 00:29:56,480
I don’t want to leave it out too long,
or the paint will fade.

473
00:29:57,120 --> 00:29:58,200
I didn’t say anything.

474
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:01,720
What about you, August?

475
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:03,200
You coming home with us?

476
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:08,000
I’ve gotta work on
an assignment with Tle, Boss Ko.

477
00:30:08,200 --> 00:30:09,120
Ah!

478
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:12,000
The guy who stole my class president title?

479
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:16,080
And August, my traitorous right-hand man.

480
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:19,520
My bad, Boss Ko.

481
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:20,920
Watch your back.

482
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:23,440
You might get murdered
and chopped into pieces.

483
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:26,200
I’m heading out now.

484
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:29,480
Tle’s gonna kill you.

485
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:31,640
See you.

486
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:33,800
See you, Ko Song.

487
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:37,200
Ko.

488
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:39,800
Wanna go for a ride?

489
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:42,240
We’ve still got assignments to do.

490
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:45,320
Jeez, you always have to disagree with me.

491
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:47,360
Other people are working too.

492
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:48,760
If we don’t do it, we’ll fall behind.

493
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:49,840
Fine.

494
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:52,080
But I’ve got conditions.

495
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:57,320
From now on, you have to
bring me oranges every day.

496
00:30:58,000 --> 00:30:58,440
Whoa.

497
00:31:00,920 --> 00:31:02,200
And pick me up in the morning.

498
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:06,200
Can we go for a bike ride instead?

499
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:08,080
Too late. You lost your chance.

500
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:10,080
You already lost that chance, mister!

501
00:31:10,320 --> 00:31:11,400
Ha ha ha.

502
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,320
Let’s go.

503
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:16,840
Come on.

504
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:22,920
- Odd one out!
- Odd one out!

505
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:36,080
Achi, aren’t you going home?

506
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:39,160
I’m waiting for my mom.

507
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:40,880
Why don’t you wait downstairs?

508
00:31:45,080 --> 00:31:46,560
I’m fine waiting here.

509
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:53,520
Scared of those seniors from the other day?

510
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:55,600
Mm.

511
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:01,760
Hey, why don’t you
wait at the basketball court instead?

512
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:04,480
My friends and I play there almost every day.

513
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:05,960
It should be more convenient for you.

514
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:12,760
Yeah, sure.

515
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:14,840
Maybe tomorrow.

516
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:16,400
Mm, see you.

517
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:23,360
Augar.

518
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:31,160
Thanks a lot.

519
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:33,200
No problem.

520
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,160
I shouldn’t have brought you oranges.

521
00:32:59,840 --> 00:33:00,680
What? What? What?

522
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:02,040
They’re my fuel.

523
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:04,640
Ko needs his energy.

524
00:33:04,880 --> 00:33:06,520
My body needs vitamins.

525
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:07,400
So many excuses.

526
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:11,480
I let you into my gang,
and you’re turning against me?

527
00:33:12,120 --> 00:33:14,240
Finish the work first, then you can eat.

528
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:16,400
Or I’m not bringing you oranges anymore.

529
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:19,920
If you don’t, I’ll just steal some.

530
00:33:20,320 --> 00:33:21,760
Your specialty, huh? Stealing.

531
00:33:22,640 --> 00:33:24,000
Hey, don’t accuse me.

532
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:25,840
Sometimes they fall on their own.

533
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:29,800
See? They practically dropped right here.

534
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:32,680
- Jeez!
- Hey!

535
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:41,320
Careful.

536
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:43,440
The ladder’s shaking.

537
00:33:43,640 --> 00:33:44,720
Why don’t you come hold it for me?

538
00:33:46,760 --> 00:33:47,880
Come on. It’s almost done anyway.

539
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:49,400
Why don’t you freaking do it yourself?

540
00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:54,280
Oh, so we’re close enough
for that kind of language now?

541
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:58,000
Pass me the bird.

542
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:02,400
Here.

543
00:34:03,840 --> 00:34:06,000
The orange tree isn’t even that tall.

544
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:07,400
Don’t be such a scaredy-cat.

545
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:09,880
Argh!

546
00:34:12,960 --> 00:34:13,920
Ouch.

547
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:15,960
Ow!

548
00:34:20,040 --> 00:34:20,720
What’re you laughing at?

549
00:34:45,080 --> 00:34:45,440
Well?

550
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:48,040
Caught anything yet, Ko?

551
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:50,760
Not yet, Dad. And I’m bored.

552
00:34:51,160 --> 00:34:53,160
Jeez. Bored, huh?

553
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:57,320
It’s normal not to catch anything.

554
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:02,360
You know, some people
spend their whole lives fishing

555
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:06,440
without realizing they were never
really after the fish.

556
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:09,840
What book did you get that from this time?

557
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,400
You really know me well, kiddo.

558
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:17,400
You’re pretty quick-witted.

559
00:35:19,440 --> 00:35:20,520
You’ve been doing this your whole life.

560
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:21,880
Ever get tired of it?

561
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:23,720
If I did, then how would we make a living?

562
00:35:24,200 --> 00:35:24,880
How would we put food on the table?

563
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:27,520
No, seriously, Dad.

564
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,720
Doing the same thing
for that long can bore you, yes.

565
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:40,040
But you know,
I’m happy every time I’m out at sea.

566
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:45,200
Every trip makes me wonder
what kind of fish I’ll bring home.

567
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,880
Dad! I got one!

568
00:35:52,120 --> 00:35:53,240
Slowly reel it in.

569
00:35:58,480 --> 00:35:59,400
This little guy?

570
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:01,040
I’ve caught millions of them.

571
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:05,760
Dad, all that matters is that it’s my first catch.

572
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:14,080
Remember this feeling, Ko.

573
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:16,600
Mm.

574
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:46,640
Ko.

575
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:49,760
New kid.

576
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:00,440
Ko!

577
00:37:11,200 --> 00:37:12,560
Wait for me tomorrow.

578
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:16,120
You want oranges?

579
00:37:16,520 --> 00:37:17,320
Yes. I want oranges.

580
00:37:18,720 --> 00:37:21,160
The oranges from your house
are the most delicious.

581
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:22,840
Okay.

582
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:27,360
Good night, Ko Number 2!

583
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:18,600
Ko Song.

584
00:38:19,880 --> 00:38:20,880
Nicely done.

585
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:28,200
Let’s go.

586
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:29,640
Ride off.

587
00:38:38,320 --> 00:38:39,360
Eating it already?

588
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,640
It’s good stuff. I’m not sharing it with anyone.

589
00:38:43,800 --> 00:38:45,000
Is it really that good?

590
00:38:45,720 --> 00:38:48,200
I don’t know about other people,
but I like oranges.

591
00:38:48,640 --> 00:38:49,640
I love them.

592
00:38:54,640 --> 00:38:55,000
Hey!

593
00:38:57,600 --> 00:38:59,160
Ko Song.

594
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:01,440
What was that for? I just dropped it.

595
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:03,960
From now on, can I call you Orange?

596
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:04,800
What?

597
00:39:05,560 --> 00:39:07,920
Why not? You gave me a nickname.

598
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:09,680
Why can’t I give you one?

599
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:11,480
Okay, Orange?

600
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:18,200
Fine. But only when we’re alone together.

601
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:19,800
Why?

602
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:21,000
Embarrassed?

603
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:23,840
A little.

604
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:26,440
Fine.

605
00:39:27,080 --> 00:39:29,040
I’ll only call you that
when we’re alone together.

606
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:30,440
Mhm-hm.

607
00:39:31,640 --> 00:39:32,400
Okay.

608
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:36,160
Let’s go, Orange. Hold on tight.

609
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:37,280
I’m gonna eat more oranges now.

610
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,040
August! Augar!

611
00:39:49,080 --> 00:39:51,560
Catch us if you can.

612
00:39:51,720 --> 00:39:52,240
Ko!

613
00:39:54,120 --> 00:39:58,600
(Toward the end of summer,
everything feels fragile and melts so easily.)

614
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:02,320
(Like ice, ice cream…)

615
00:40:04,400 --> 00:40:09,720
(or even someone’s hardened heart.)

616
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:15,920
♪ Every time that we meet again ♪

617
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:19,520
♪ Something grows a little more each day ♪

618
00:40:19,880 --> 00:40:21,240
Hey, wait up!

619
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:23,520
Keep up, Augar! August!

620
00:40:25,120 --> 00:40:28,120
♪ Might not be too far away at all ♪

621
00:40:28,320 --> 00:40:32,160
♪ Even when winter fades I’ll still wait on ♪

622
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:35,000
[KO SONG’S DESK]

623
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:36,560
Sit here forever.

624
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:40,040
I’m saving this spot just for you.

625
00:40:40,720 --> 00:40:47,200
♪ I fear nothing if this season has you ♪

626
00:41:07,160 --> 00:41:09,520
So your parents leave early every day?

627
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:11,640
You can come eat at my house.

628
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:14,680
Try some Kaeng Som, dear.

629
00:41:15,120 --> 00:41:16,160
Thank you, ma’am.

630
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:18,040
Actually, Orang— oops!

631
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:22,680
Augar! August! Execute him!

632
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:27,320
Want to go study in my room?

633
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,240
Come take a look.

634
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:31,160
The view of your room from my window.
